# Reference

API references live outside this site, one per language binding:

- **Rust:** [docs.rs/eunoia](https://docs.rs/eunoia/) (rustdoc, the
  authoritative reference for every public type, trait, and function).
- **JavaScript/TypeScript:** the [JavaScript API
  reference](/docs/reference/javascript/) catalogs the public surface, and full
  type definitions ship with
  [`@jolars/eunoia`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@jolars/eunoia) so your
  editor's "go to definition"/IntelliSense will surface them.
- **Python:** the [`eunoia` Python API
  reference](https://jolars.github.io/eunoia-py/).
- **R:** the [eulerr reference](https://jolars.github.io/eulerr/), now backed by
  the eunoia engine.
- **Julia:** the [`Eunoia.jl`
  reference](https://jolars.github.io/Eunoia.jl/stable).
- **Repository conventions:** [CONTRIBUTING.md](https://github.com/jolars/eunoia/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md)
  describes how to set up the workspace, run the test and lint gates, and submit
  changes.

The chapters under [Concepts](/docs/concepts/label-placement/) and
[Bindings](/docs/bindings/c-abi/) cover the *why* and the
*how*; use them alongside the rustdoc/tsdoc, not in place of them.
